label.value: pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition

definition.value: A categorical value specification that is a  pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

label.value: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition

definition.value: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) v7 staging systems.

label.value: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification

definition.value: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a gynecologic cancer according to the International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics (FIGO) staging systems.

label.value: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification

definition.value: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the FIGO classification system.
A categorical value specification that is an assessment of a participant's performance status (general well-being and activities of daily life).

label.value: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification

definition.value: A performance status value specification designed by the Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group to assess disease progression and its affect on the daily living abilities of the patient.
A performance status value specification designed for classifying patients 16 years of age or older by their functional impairment.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer.
A clinical history in which there was no diagnosis of cancer.
A clinical history in which it is not known whether there was a diagnosis of cancer.
A diagnosis that is an assertion that a patient who is the subject of a diagnostic process has cancer.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a blood relative.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in the female sibling of a parent.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a male sibling.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a person's female child.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a male parent.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a female parent.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a female sibling.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a person's male child.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a male sibling of a parent.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a female parent of a parent.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a male parent of a parent.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a male child of a sibling.
A clinical history in which there is a diagnosis of cancer in a female child of a sibling.
A diagnosis that is an assertion that a patient who is the subject of a diagnostic process has an infectious disease.
A diagnosis of infectious disease caused by the hepatitis B virus.
A diagnosis of infectious disease caused by the hepatitis C virus.
A diagnosis of infectious disease caused by the human immunodeficiency virus (1 or 2).

label.value: clinical history of repeated HIV assays

definition.value: A clinical history in which there is repeated reactive screening assays for human immunodeficiency virus (1 or 2) antibodies regardless of the results of supplemental assays.
A clinical history in which there has been second hand exposure to tobacco smoking.

label.value: exposure to second hand smoke in household during childhood

definition.value: An exposure to second hand smoke that occurred in the (patient's) household when the person was a child.

label.value: exposure to second hand smoke in current household

definition.value: An exposure to second hand smoke in person's current household.
A clinical history in which a female has had a pregnancy.
A measurement datum of the total number of pregnancies a woman has had.
A measurement datum of the total number of live births a female has had.

label.value: age when gave birth to first child

definition.value: An age measurement datum performed on a female when her first biological child was born.
A clinical history in which a woman has had gynecologic surgery in the past.
A gynecologic surgery history in which a woman has had a hysterectomy.
A gynecologic surgery history in which a woman has had a unilateral oophorectomy.
A gynecologic surgery history in which a woman has not had either a hysterectomy or an oophorectomy.
An information content entity that indicates whether a woman has ever used oral contraceptives in order to block ovulation and prevent the occurrence of pregnancy.

label.value: hormonal birth control former use history

definition.value: A hormonal birth control use history that indicates an individual has previously been a hormonal birth control user but is not a current user.

label.value: hormonal birth control current use history

definition.value: A hormonal birth control use history that indicates an individual is currently a hormonal birth control user.

label.value: no hormonal birth control use history

definition.value: A hormonal birth control use history that indicates an individual has not ever been a hormonal birth control user.
A clinical history in which an individual has had hormonal replacement therapy in the past.

label.value: delivery form for hormonal replacement therapy

definition.value: A processed material used for delivery of hormones in hormone replacement therapy.

label.value: pill delivery form for hormonal replacement therapy

definition.value: A delivery form for hormonal replacement therapy that is a pill for oral administration.

label.value: patch delivery form for hormonal replacement therapy

definition.value: A delivery form for hormonal replacement therapy that is a patch for transdermal administration.

label.value: cream delivery form for hormonal replacement therapy

definition.value: A delivery form for hormonal replacement therapy that is a cream for transdermal administration.
An information content entity that indicates the state of a female's cessation of menstruation.
